{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"163bcdfc-18cf-4604-b5ab-b3e77e3b0aeb","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but your project targets:\n\n| Target Framework | MSTest v3 Compatible? |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Yes |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **No** — .NET 5 is out of support; MSTest v3 requires net6.0+ |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **No** — not supported by MSTest v3 |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n1. Replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or newer)\n2. Remove `netcoreapp3.1` (or upgrade to `net6.0`+)\n3. Update the MSTest packages to v3 (e.g., `3.x`)\n\nIf you still need to test against those older frameworks, you'll have to keep a separate MSTest v2 configuration for them.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c15a3455-a2c4-4d43-b317-68db9f67d7fc","outputTokens":242,"requestId":"0C01:14FF5F:6304C93:6C582B8:69F01EAF"},"id":"ff2fdc14-372c-443e-b0d4-41179d47dae2","timestamp":"2026-04-28T02:43:02.105Z","parentId":"bac7a7a3-1973-43fe-ae15-97afbb413a35"}
